Title: On the Persistence of Knowledge and Ignorance: A Preliminary Report  
Author: Fangzhen Lin Yoav Shoham 
Address: Toronto, Canada M5S 1A4  Stanford, CA 94305  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science University of Toronto  Department of Computer Science Stanford University  
Abstract: We study a particular model of the way in which a single agent's knowledge evolves over time. The two fundamental properties of the model are that knowledge always persists (i.e., agents have perfect memory), and that ignorance persists by default (i.e., we have complete knowledge of exactly how much the agent learns at every time point). Despite its apparent simplicity, this model exhibits quite complex properties.
